{"type":"message","id":"afea3bdc","parentId":"0873501c","timestamp":"2026-05-12T19:00:46.607Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The browser status shows \"device identity required\" error. The user is asking why the browser isn't working and what the canvas setting is for.\n\nLet me explain the situation: the browser tool requires device identity/authentication through the Gateway. The canvas is a separate feature for hosting web-based content. The user's Ubuntu system has a visual desktop, and they want to know why the browser can't be used.\n\nThe error says \"device identity required\" - this means the Gateway needs to authenticate with the browser. The canvas setting is different from the browser tool.","thinkingSignature":"ddd91d6b048c4e4b3aeb84f46dc075690bcc7f22ed1567c0cc3a47708020fe21"},{"type":"text","text":"browser 工具确实没打开 — 报错 `device identity required`，意思是 Gateway 需要和浏览器进行设备认证才能控制它。\n\ncanvas 和 browser 是两套东西：\n- **canvas** — 用来呈现/托管网页内容（是个轻量的内置 web 服务器）\n- **browser** — 真正控制用户的浏览器（需要设备认证）\n\n你的可视化 Ubuntu 系统上，Gateway 跑在本地，但控制浏览器需要先\"配对认证\"。你现在是怎么运行 OpenClaw 的？是直接在那个 Ubuntu 桌面环境里跑 Gateway 吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4380,"output":223,"cacheRead":15508,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20111,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778612431001,"responseId":"0652abcf1b399507dcbb0ba23e0da1a3"}}
